<p>I am a firm believer of the whole &quot;Earth for teh win for solo&quot; saying. Earth can root, making it pretty handy from the start, the help prevent adds. Also, it has alot of HP's. Yes, it gets hit often. Yes, it doesn't stun. Thats where the little tactic of CHAIN SUMMONING comes in. <br /> <br />The whole &quot;Get earth pet, do damage, earth gets low on health, start to summon a new one, press go away, new pet , full hps pops up!&quot; thing?? Of course, you then set him to attack mob straight away (it's rooted),&nbsp;&nbsp;cast BO and a DS on him, sorted. <br /> <br />Fire is good if you need a certain drop in a Low zone. Say your level 52. Brand new Fire pet, and say your working on Najena.  Use your fire pet, the mobs will kill themselves. <br /> <br />Water, as stated is good for fighting snakes and spiders, but whats the point if you can just click a level 8 heal spell a voila! Poison gone? <br /> <br />Air is only handy in groups in my opinion. Stuns help groups lots, aye, stuns help solo abit, but why bother? Earth pet will take care of it. Air doesn't get hit alot - so what ? CHAIN SUMMON! <br /> <br /> <br />Of course, theres always the alternative which I prefer called &quot;get a group&quot;.. ;)</p>
