<p>Earth pet is best for soloing i think. Burnout 5 with focus aug/item and add a damage shield to it and its a great tank. Especially good if your soloing more than 1 mob at a time...you can use the pets root as CC if you know how to do it right. (This works best with velocity...otherwise pet gets the crap kicked outta him trying to move from the rooted mob to the other). <br /> <br />In a group id go with water. By far the bets dps. Make sure to let the water pet get the back of the mob your fighting. Ask the tank to help with this or just park your pet so it runs into the mobs back every pull. <br /> <br />Ive actually never used fire...so wont give any info on it. <br /> <br />Air pet is great for a group facing alot of casters. The air pet's stun will interupt casting and allow the tank to get a couple extra hits in b4 he get hit again. I wouldnt use the air pet for tanking because its hps do seem to drop very quickly especially at higher levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />Toket Firehurler <br />Magician of the 65th season</p>
