		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=169546"><span class="Scholar">Angg</span></a><b><span class="Scholar"><br/>Scholar</span></b><br />46 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=Angg;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>It all depends on the situation. <br /> <br />Earth - Personally, I almost never use the earth pet.&nbsp;&nbsp;The root only serves to cause the group and/or pet more damage since the mob stays fighting until the bitter end.  I only use in group when we don't have someone to snare or when soloing a mob way above my level where I will be cannipetting to kill.  The extra hp's here help save on the mana because he stays alive a bit longer. <br /> <br />Air - awesome pet used on casters - those wonderful blasts of air that stun the mob may save you and your pet's butt from those nasty nukers.  A pretty good group pet as well since the stuns also help keep the MOB dps down. <br /> <br />Fire - If you have a mob that hits fast but not hard, why not use that so called useless fire pet.  The DS on the fire pet is on spell level above the one you can cast and it will eat up that mob. <br /> <br />Water - on my retired mage I didn't use water much until post 51.  Then he turned into a nasty little rogue.  Wanna impress your group with your pet, turn taunt off (actually not that necessary to do as your pet prob won't get aggro), circle around back of the mob and have your pet attack the back.  Watch as the backstabs begin to flow.  They aren't as often as a regular rogue but this little beastie hits hard and will land a few 200+ backstabs to boot.  That extra dps is awefully helpful in a group especially when you are fighting something with alot of hp. <br /> <br />So there it is...personally I will be utilizing my fire pet up until 51 (others only in select occasions) then after that, the majority will be water or air. <br /> <br />Good luck, get a horse or some jboots and Godspeed. <br /> <br /></p>
